cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.DM, cs.AL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with network design problems. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes a new counting argument for the iterated rounding based 2-approximation. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the hypergraphic version of SNDP. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with graph theory and combinatorial optimization. 
- cs.AL (Computational Geometry) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve geometric interpretations of network design problems.
